Belgium,[b] officially the Kingdom of Belgium,[c] is a country in
Northwestern Europe. Situated in a coastal lowland region known as
the Low Countries, it is bordered by the Netherlands to the north, Germany
to the east, Luxembourg to the southeast, France to the south, and the
North Sea to the west. Belgium covers an area of 30,689 km2
(11,849 sq mi)[4] and has a population of more than 11.8 million.